Sassarin spewed out a jet of flame, the tall Slark ignited a small patch of forest, then hovered above it, waiting for the right moment. But what was strange was that when he slowed down, the eerie screams coming from behind him stopped as well. Sassarin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenrou, you've turned into a Slime before!"
"It's one thing to fly by myself and quite another to be carried off by a gigantic pink dragon unexpectedly."
"Are you okay, Kayel?"
Kael looked clearly unimpressed by Nisi's words, and appeared even paler than usual, his claws plunged deeply into Sazalin's back, drawing blood from the slarks, but Sazalin seemed utterly unaffected.
"I'm sorry, I smell something. I have to take care of it!"
"Why must you drag us along too?" Tenuk climbed down from Sasaquin's back, slid down the tail and landed on the ground, his voice sharp with question. "We left Retevik behind! We abandoned that strong and fierce giant! How can he possibly find us?"
"He'll figure it out...," Nix said, nodding in satisfaction. "Rettick is slow, but he's not dumb."
"Will Reetvik drive?"
Nisi blinked her eyes, turned her head to look at Tenoku. "Of course, he will drive."
Have you ever seen Rettwick drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive a car as cute as Kayel's, he started taking the bus to work because you always drive us to school. He only has a bicycle.
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sashlin suddenly couldn't help but laugh out loud, but no one knew what he was laughing about. It took Sashlin a while to calm down.
"I'm so sorry, I just imagined something, you in armor, riding a bike designed for children from Temsion. The picture is hilarious! I wish I had telepathy, this idea is so interesting! I'll definitely treasure it!"
Kayer also laughed because he could imagine what Sazalin was thinking. "Okay, okay. But what exactly did you smell, and why did you fly so fast?"
Sasarin let out a whistle, and after taking off, he quickly disappeared and then flew back, dropping a corpse in front of Nisi. It was an Orosaral, a very rare gold and white dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. "Another one dead. I heard their cries. Smelled their blood. I have to protect them, hunt down the killer. This is Isini's will. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slark stood frozen. Nix and Kael also froze, their attention drawn to a gap on the edge of the clearing. A massive and jet-black thing loomed over them, emitting a screech. It suddenly spread two enormous wings, charging forward with its sights set on Sazol, completely disregarding the three little creatures between it and Sazol. Kael and Tenok barely managed to dodge to the side, but Nix found himself knocked to the ground, almost flung onto Sazol.
Sasarin grabbed Nisi with one hand, using his long and agile tail to throw her onto his back, and then he leaped into the air. A black, two-winged creature swiftly chased after.
Kayelet let out a breath, pulled out a rifle from his back, then opened the bag, taking out a belt of bullets. He hung the belt across his chest, convenient for access, but soon realized that Nixie, Sazalin, and the monster were nowhere to be seen.
"Hey, T'Nuk, can you shape-shift into a flying animal?" Kayel asked.
"Do you want to go after it?"
"Nonsense."
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? The firepower of this rifle in my hand is strong, and I can fire it at any time. I just need to see it, and I can shoot it down."
Tu'nuk hesitated for a moment, then stepped back a pace, giving himself some space. As a low, slightly pained groan echoed through the air, Tu'nuk's body stretched out, his fur transforming into scales, his arms into wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, pale blue Slark, but his eyes remained red.
"Come on up."
Tenuk now looks like a fairly ordinary Slithzer, with neat rows of scales on his back and a pair of sharp spines that made it easier for Cayel to grasp. Tenuk took a long time to take to the air, but once airborne, he quickly adjusted his direction and strained to catch up.
However, Tenruk and Kayel soon realized they were not facing a single opponent. A second dark monster burst forth from beneath them, and Tenruk narrowly dodged the impact.
"I guess this is the other terrible monster Ranecks is worried about?" Cayel furrowed his brow, trying to shoot at the second monster, but missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not respond, he was busy heading towards Nisi and Salarin, despite another monster was chasing after them. Kayel clumsily turned around, facing the monster. The monster was still chasing, Kayel thought this was a good news, because he could get a better aim and shoot. Two bullets pierced through the monster's upper wing, it let out a painful howl before disappearing into the woods. Kayel was unsure if it was still following them, but he felt it was sure to be lagging behind.
In front of them, Sasaarin was wildly flailing his body, spewing fire at the black monster, while Nisi desperately clung to him, trying to prevent them from falling. Although this beast was clearly wounded, it seemed to have been enraged, unwilling to retreat, and the fireballs seemed to have inflicted minimal damage. Sasaarin regained his balance, and Nisi seized the opportunity to draw his weapon - a shotgun she trusted. Of course, the shotgun wouldn't be able to take down this kind of monster, but the scattered bullets might at least scare the black beast away.
